Djokovic Wins First Set 6-2 Against Nadal in U.S. Open Men’s Tennis Final

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-09-12T21:08:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/djokovic-wins-first-set-6-2-against-nadal-in-u-s-open-men-s-tennis-final.html
Top seed Novak Djokovic of  Serbia 
has won the first set 6-2 against defending champion  Rafael
Nadal  of  Spain  in the U.S. Open men’s tennis final.  After losing the first two games of the match, Djokovic
broke Nadal’s serve three straight times while winning the next
six games.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  